# Changelog

All notable changes to this project will be documented in this file.

## [3.0.0] - 2025-06-15

### Added

-   Memory for the voice agent to store entire conversations and respond accordingly.
-   Default greeting from the voice agent for a more natural call experience.
-   `.env` file-driven configurations to easily change models for components.

## [2.0.0] - 2025-06-14

### Added

-   Integration of the `silero-vad` package for Voice Activity Detection (VAD).
-   Dynamic buffering of audio data from Twilio until the user stops talking, replacing the fixed window size buffer from v1.

## [1.0.0] - 2025-06-13

### Added

-   Initial version using Twilio and SarvamAI for telephony conversations.
-   Twilio's Bi-directional media stream on WebSocket for raw audio processing through the pipeline:
    -   Speech-To-Text (STT)
    -   Large Language Model (LLM)
    -   Text-To-Speech (TTS)
-   Streaming audio responses back to Twilio.
-   Fixed chunk size audio processing (e.g., every 10 seconds or based on `window_size`).
